<center><table border=0><tr><td><center><H2><font face=arial>Give the AI programer more credit...</font></H2></center>
<font face=arial size=2><b>Posted By:</b> <A HREF="/cgi-local/whois2.cgi?Azure">Azure</a><br>
<b>Posted On:</b> 7:19 p.m. 9/2/1999<br>
<b>Subject:</b> Give the AI programer more credit...<p>
<br><center><img src="http://www.everworld.net/pvpquest/images/divider.gif" width=452 height=22 border=0></center><BR><P ALIGN=CENTER><b>In Reply To:</b> <A HREF="http://www.everworld.net/cgi-local/pvp.cgi?read=452" TARGET=_self>Re: Wait a minute here...</A> (Koss)
</STRONG><FONT SIZE=2 color=#FFFFFF FACE=arial>
<P>It wouldnt be very hard to make a list of all the things that lower your reputation. Besides being the first to attack another player, or stealing from others, there really isnt much else.

<P>I cant think of any situations where a player with a good reputation could get a bad reputation unless he wanted to. If he wanted to get a bad reputation, he should expect to have the guards come after him if they should see him.
<P>But as i have said before, the only way we will find out for sure what will work, is by testing it out. So in less than 24 hours we can test all the ideas people have come up with "providing EQ will allow us the time", and find a balanced solution to the +PvP delema.
<P>&gt; No, thats not what I meant at all.
<P>&gt; Its quite easy for monsters to go around killing all the
<BR>&gt; "Do-baders", the problem is that NPCs cant determine
<BR>&gt; what is bad and what is good. There are way too many forms of
<BR>&gt; "bad" and "good". If you make a NPC that
<BR>&gt; goes around killing just bad people, there are going to be
<BR>&gt; countless good people who are going to be killed by these tough
<BR>&gt; NPC's because the NPC is just too dumb to know if the person is
<BR>&gt; good or bad.
<P>&gt; I would much rather be killed by a player killer than killed by
<BR>&gt; a super NPC who kills me for doing something that the NPC
<BR>&gt; considers "bad". While it might be possible for Verant
<BR>&gt; to lay out a complicated list of "good things", and
<BR>&gt; "bad things", this list would have to be HUGE and near
<BR>&gt; impossible for anyone to understand everything on it.
<BR>
</FONT></td></tr></table></P>
